The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Saturday, June 26, 2004 				 Parthiv gets a job off the field
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Ahmedabad, June 25: Parthiv Patel, the youngest Indian playing Test cricket, today joined Reliance Industries Ltd as an executive handling sports and culture.																								The wicketkeeper was inducted at a simple ceremony here when he signed and exchanged documents with Parimal Nathwani, Reliances executive in charge of Gujarat.																								I am both humbled and enthusiastic about joining Reliance, which has inducted me just at the onset of my career, Parthiv said in the presence of his family. 																								He accepted the offer, made 45 days ago, after being assured that the job would not hamper his on-field career.																								Parthiv had just turned 19 this April when he scored a matchwinning 69 against Pakistan in the third and final test.
